definitions.definition: A competitor thought unlikely to win .
examples: They were the underdogs in the basketball competition.

definitions.definition: A high swing wherein the person pushing the swing runs beneath the swing while the person being pushed is at the forward limit of the arc .

main_definition: A competitor thought unlikely to win .
secondary_definitions: A high swing wherein the person pushing the swing runs beneath the swing while the person being pushed is at the forward limit of the arc .
